💍 Top Bridal Makeup Tips from a Makeup Artist

1. Start Skincare Early
Begin a consistent skincare routine 3–6 months before the big day. Hydration is key!

2. Do a Makeup Trial
Book a trial to test your look in natural and flash lighting—bring inspo pics!

3. Know Your Style
Go for a look that enhances *your* beauty. If you’re a natural girl, keep it soft and timeless.

4. Prime to Last
Good prep = flawless makeup. Use hydrating or mattifying primers based on your skin type.

5. Waterproof is a Must
Emotions happen—choose waterproof mascara and long-wear formulas for everything.

6. Groom Your Brows
Shape them 5–7 days before the wedding. Don’t overdo it or try a new shape last minute!

7. Touch-Up Kit
Keep essentials like lipstick, blotting paper, and powder for quick fixes.

8. Blend Everything
Make sure makeup is blended into your neck and chest for a seamless finish.

9. Sleep & Hydrate
Water and rest = glowing skin. Don’t skip them in the final days!

10. Trust Your Artist
Choose someone you vibe with—and let them take care of you on the day.
